Teaser trailer for my new short film “Je t’aime, Julie” directed by my brother and I! 

Based on the real life chronicles of Julie D’Aubigny, a bisexual swords woman in the late 17th century, the short follows Julie as she resorts to desperate ways to be reunited with her lover who’s become a nun at a convent. 

Everyone’s support on this has been unreal and I can’t thank you all enough ♥️ This festival run is going to be huge, I can’t wait to update you all on everything! 

To the entire cast & crew, thank you all so so so much, my love for you is eternal ♥️

i love women 

📸 by me

beginning of 2023 was tough, but it was the year i focused 100% on my creative work behind the camera which was scary. 

here’s what i accomplished though: 

- directed 5 music videos 
- my work for @sarahkinsleyd was on a billboard in time square
- went on tour as a photographer w/ @julyjones 
- finished and submitted our short film “Je t’aime, Julie” to festivals 
- took photos for some amazing artists and models 
- creative directed photoshoots and artists 
- got my work put in a magazine 

i accomplished so much with little to no understanding on what the fuck i was even doing but now i’m here and i can’t wait to see what 2024 has to offer for me xx 

thanks for being there and supporting me through it all 🖤
